description.narrative: UNICEF continued supporting Government of Mozambique to increase access to safe drinking water in rural areas and small towns. Despite some delays in the implementation of its development related interventions due to the shifting of priorities following the cyclones Idai and Kenneth, the UNICEF WASH program managed to reach and surpass its overall targets for the year. Through UNICEF technical and financial support, 617 boreholes and 17 water supply systems (including climate resilient solar powered systems) were completed in 2019 reaching over 235,000 people at various service levels. Additionally, the WASH in HF initiative gained momentum during 2019. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2020
